The topics of the lectures and seminars of the Environmental Law course include the development of environmental law, the goals of environmental protection and environmental values, the main concepts and principles of environmental law, the levels of environmental regulation, the means of regulating environmental law, the rights and obligations related to the environment, compliance with environmental norms and verification thereof, environmental responsibility, and the foundations of regulating the most important fields of the special part of environmental law. The course includes learning about the court practice of the European Court of Human Rights, the Court of Justice of the European Union, and Estonian courts.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the Environmental Law course is to teach the theoretical bases of environmental law, explain the main concepts and principles of environmental law and the system of environmental rights and obligations, as well as to give an overview of the means of regulating environmental law and the most important levels of legal control over environmental nuisances.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  By the end of the course, the student will: 1. know the main terms of environmental law and be able to explain the content of the most important principles of environmental law; 2. be able to apply the most important principles of environmental law in solving problems related to the field; 3. know the connections between environmental law in Estonia, the EU, and globally; 4. have an overview of the main institutions of environmental law and understand their connections to other fields of law; 5. know the system of legal means for environmental nuisances and understand its functioning; 6. know the foundations of the most important fields of the special part of environmental law.
